+# Automation Support for Homepage & Themes — Next Gen Portal
+
+**Epic:** [PORTAL-10](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/PORTAL-10) (Idea, High)  
+**PRD:** [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1_7vNuEIkqluevxTrkfTIzlQJ9iH3lgUdc7hBG7WLbuE/edit) *(internal)*  
+**Related:** [APIM-14003](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/APIM-14003) (navigation automation — Done), [APIM-14029](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/APIM-14029) (homepage cover image / CI/CD pain)
+
+---
+
+## Problem statement
+
+Gravitee shipped **partial** next-gen portal automation via the Automation API ([APIM-14003](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/APIM-14003)): portals, `TOP_NAVBAR` navigation, API listings, and documentation pages can be managed as code through GitOps, Terraform, or GKO.
+
+Two **global, environment-scoped** surfaces that define the consumer's first impression are still **Console-only**:
+
+| Surface | What it controls | Automation today |
+|--------|------------------|------------------|
+| **Homepage** | Landing page at `/` (GMD content, publish state) | ❌ None |
+| **Theme** | Branding — colors, font, logo, favicon, custom CSS | ❌ None |
+
+**Impact:** Platform teams running Kubernetes, GitOps, or immutable CI/CD cannot fully provision or promote a branded developer portal without manual steps in Gamma Console or classic APIM Console. Navigation and API catalog can be automated, but the **landing experience and visual identity cannot** — leaving a broken "infrastructure-as-code" story for enterprise deployments.
+
+This was an explicit deferral in the GKO hybrid model ([APIM-14008](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/APIM-14008)): *"Scope is `TOP_NAVBAR` only. `HOMEPAGE` is out of scope until the rest is stable."* With navigation automation now delivered, homepage and themes are the next gap.
+
+A related pain point ([APIM-14029](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/APIM-14029)): homepage cover images and media in GMD content have no CI/CD-friendly path — no upload in Portal Next editor, `portal.uploadMedia.enabled` does not apply, forcing external hosting or undocumented workarounds.
+
+---
+
+## Personas
+
+### 1. Platform Engineer (primary)
+
+- Runs APIM on Kubernetes with GKO / ArgoCD / Terraform
+- Owns environment bootstrap, promotion pipelines, and disaster recovery
+- **Goal:** Declare the full portal consumer experience in Git — navigation **and** branding **and** homepage — with idempotent, reviewable changes
+
+### 2. API Platform Owner / Portal Administrator (secondary)
+
+- Owns developer portal content and brand guidelines
+- May use Console for ad-hoc edits but wants Git as source of truth for prod
+- **Goal:** Version-controlled homepage and theme that can be reviewed, rolled back, and promoted across environments
+
+### 3. Enterprise Customer on immutable infrastructure
+
+- No manual Console access in prod; all changes via pipeline
+- **Goal:** Reproducible portal branding and landing page on every environment rebuild without UI dependency
+
+---
+
+## Use cases
+
+| # | Use case | Actor |
+|---|----------|-------|
+| UC-1 | **Bootstrap a new environment** with default navigation, branded theme, and welcome homepage from a single Git repo / Terraform module | Platform Engineer |
+| UC-2 | **Promote portal branding** (colors, logo, homepage copy) from dev → staging → prod via CI/CD pipeline | Platform Engineer |
+| UC-3 | **Disaster recovery / rebuild** — recreate identical portal look-and-feel from declarative config | Platform Engineer |
+| UC-4 | **Multi-environment consistency** — ensure all environments share the same corporate theme and homepage structure, with environment-specific overrides (e.g. different hero image URL) | API Platform Owner |
+| UC-5 | **GitOps reconciliation** — GKO applies `PortalTheme` / `PortalHomepage` CRDs; drift from Console edits is detectable and overwritable | Platform Engineer |
+| UC-6 | **Homepage content with assets** — reference cover images and icons via stable URLs or bundled assets in GMD, without Console upload | Platform Engineer |
+| UC-7 | **Complete the automation story** started by APIM-14003 — navigation + listings + docs + **homepage + theme** = full consumer portal as code | Platform Engineer |
+
+---
+
+## State of the product today
+
+### What works (manual / Console)
+
+**Homepage**
+
+- One `HOMEPAGE` navigation item per environment (uniqueness enforced server-side)
+- Content is GMD (`portal-page-contents`) linked to that nav item
+- Edited in Console via GMD editor; publish/unpublish supported
+- Portal-next renders it at `/` via `homepageContentResolver` → first `HOMEPAGE` item + content
+- New environments get a default homepage from `default-portal-homepage-content.md`
+
+**Theme (`PORTAL_NEXT`)**
+
+- Loaded at runtime: `GET /theme?type=PORTAL_NEXT`
+- Managed in Console: `GET/PUT .../ui/themes` with `ThemePortalNext`
+- Supports: primary/secondary/tertiary/error colors, page/card backgrounds, font family, custom CSS, logo, favicon
+
+### What works (automation — already shipped)
+
+| Automation API resource | Scope |
+|------------------------|-------|
+| `PUT .../portals` | Portal identity + `TOP_NAVBAR` folder tree |
+| `PUT .../portals/{hrid}/listings` | API catalog placement |
+| `PUT .../portals/{hrid}/documentations` | GMD/OpenAPI/AsyncAPI pages in nav |
+
+Sync pipeline is hardcoded to `PortalArea.TOP_NAVBAR` only — homepage and theme are not in the Automation OpenAPI spec.
+
+### Gaps
+
+| Area | Management v2 / Console | Automation API | GKO / Terraform |
+|------|-------------------------|----------------|-----------------|
+| Homepage GMD content | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
+| Homepage publish state | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
+| `PORTAL_NEXT` theme (colors, font, CSS) | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
+| Theme assets (logo, favicon) | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
+| Homepage media / cover images (CI/CD) | ⚠️ Workarounds only | ❌ | ❌ |
+
+**MCP (portal-next):** `portal_get_theme` and navigation read APIs exist; no write/automation tools.
+
+---
+
+## Proposed solution
+
+Extend the **Automation API** (and downstream GKO CRDs / Terraform provider) to cover homepage and theme as **first-class, environment-scoped global resources** — consistent with the model established in APIM-14003 and the "global vs API-specific" split described there.
+
+```mermaid
+flowchart LR
+  subgraph git [Git / CI / Terraform]
+    themeYaml[PortalTheme spec]
+    homepageYaml[PortalHomepage spec]
+  end
+
+  subgraph automation [Automation API]
+    themePut[PUT /themes]
+    homepagePut[PUT /portals/.../homepage or PUT /homepage]
+  end
+
+  subgraph backend [Management v2 backend]
+    uiThemes[ui/themes PORTAL_NEXT]
+    navItems[portal-navigation-items HOMEPAGE]
+    pageContent[portal-page-contents]
+  end
+
+  subgraph runtime [Portal Next]
+    portalUI[Consumer portal /]
+  end
+
+  themeYaml --> themePut --> uiThemes --> portalUI
+  homepageYaml --> homepagePut --> navItems --> portalUI
+  homepagePut --> pageContent --> portalUI
+```
+
+### Homepage automation
+
+- Expose homepage as an Automation API resource (either embedded in `PortalSpec` or as a sibling resource under the portal HRID)
+- Sync creates/updates the single `HOMEPAGE` `portal-navigation-item` and its linked `portal-page-content`
+- Content: inline GMD string and/or `valueFrom`-style reference for GKO (ConfigMap/Secret pattern, aligned with `PortalContent` CRD)
+- Support `published` state
+- Respect **one homepage per environment** constraint
+
+### Theme automation
+
+- Expose `ThemeSpec` for `type: PORTAL_NEXT`, mirroring `ThemePortalNext` / `PortalNextDefinition`:
+  - Colors (primary, secondary, tertiary, error, page/card backgrounds)
+  - Font family
+  - Custom CSS
+  - Logo and favicon (base64 inline, URL, or K8s secret/configMap ref for GKO)
+- Idempotent `PUT` by HRID; updates the environment's active `PORTAL_NEXT` theme
+
+### Design principles (aligned with APIM-14003 / APIM-14008)
+
+- **Declarative, idempotent** — same PUT semantics as existing portal automation resources
+- **HRID-based** — stable references for GitOps and cross-resource linking
+- **Console parity** — anything automatable via API must match what Console can do today
+- **Classic portal untouched** — `PORTAL` (legacy) theme and pages remain unaffected
+- **Established-portal guardrails** — reuse `PortalAutomationScopeDomainService` patterns where applicable
+- **GKO path** — new CRDs (e.g. `PortalTheme`, `PortalHomepage`) or extensions to existing portal CRDs, reconciling against Automation API / Management v2
+
+---
+
+## Requirements
+
+### Functional — Homepage
+
+| ID | Requirement |
+|----|-------------|
+| H-1 | Automation API SHALL support create/update of the environment's single `HOMEPAGE` navigation item and its GMD content |
+| H-2 | Homepage content SHALL support `GRAVITEE_MARKDOWN` (GMD) as the page type |
+| H-3 | Homepage SHALL support a `published` boolean (visible to consumers when true) |
+| H-4 | Automation SHALL enforce at most one top-level `HOMEPAGE` item per environment |
+| H-5 | Homepage content SHALL be retrievable via `GET` (read-back for GitOps drift detection) |
+| H-6 | Homepage spec SHALL support inline content and external content reference (for GKO `valueFrom`) |
+| H-7 | Homepage automation SHALL NOT affect `TOP_NAVBAR` navigation sync (orthogonal areas) |
+| H-8 | Deleting/removing homepage automation resource SHALL have defined semantics (orphan vs delete remote) |
+
+### Functional — Theme
+
+| ID | Requirement |
+|----|-------------|
+| T-1 | Automation API SHALL support create/update of the active `PORTAL_NEXT` theme for an environment |
+| T-2 | Theme spec SHALL include all fields in `PortalNextDefinition`: colors, font, customCss |
+| T-3 | Theme spec SHALL support logo and favicon (binary or URL/reference) |
+| T-4 | Theme automation SHALL only target `PORTAL_NEXT`; classic `PORTAL` theme MUST NOT be modified |
+| T-5 | Theme SHALL be retrievable via `GET` for drift detection |
+| T-6 | Theme updates SHALL be reflected on next portal load (`GET /theme?type=PORTAL_NEXT`) without Console interaction |
+
+### API & integration
+
+| ID | Requirement |
+|----|-------------|
+| A-1 | OpenAPI spec updated in `gravitee-apim-rest-api-automation/.../open-api.yaml` (API-first) |
+| A-2 | Core domain services sync Automation spec → Management v2 (`ui/themes`, `portal-navigation-items`, `portal-page-contents`) |
+| A-3 | MapStruct mappers and CRD models updated per Automation API sync checklist in `gravitee-apim-rest-api/AGENTS.md` |
+| A-4 | Idempotent `PUT` by HRID; HRID preserved on update |
+| A-5 | Integration/contract tests for homepage and theme automation endpoints |
+| A-6 | GKO CRD definitions and controllers (follow-on; can be phased after Automation API) |
+| A-7 | Terraform provider resource mapping (follow-on; depends on Automation API) |
+
+### Non-functional
+
+| ID | Requirement |
+|----|-------------|
+| NF-1 | Backward compatible — existing Console-managed homepages/themes continue to work |
+| NF-2 | No breaking changes to Portal consumer API (`/theme`, `/portal-navigation-items`) |
+| NF-3 | Authentication/authorization aligned with existing Automation API patterns |
+| NF-4 | Classic portal behavior unchanged |
+
+### Out of scope (v1)
+
+- Multi-portal-per-environment homepage/theme (gated by `automation.portal.allowMultiplePortalPerEnv`; materialization today skips non-default portals)
+- Console UX changes for homepage/theme authoring
+- Native media upload in Portal Next GMD editor ([APIM-14029](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/APIM-14029) — related but separate)
+- `portal.next.banner.*` environment parameters (future consideration)
+
+---
+
+## Context: what navigation automation already solved
+
+[APIM-14003](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/APIM-14003) established the foundation this epic builds on:
+
+- Bridge the automation gap for CI/CD, Terraform, and GKO in next-gen portal (4.11+)
+- Distinguish **global resources** (navigation, themes) from **API-specific resources** (docs, sub-nav)
+- Unified conceptual model across UI and API
+- Backward compatibility with Classic Portal
+
+Navigation is **Done**. Homepage and themes are the remaining **global resources** called out in that epic but not yet exposed through automation.
+
+---
+
+## Suggested phasing
+
+| Phase | Deliverable |
+|-------|-------------|
+| **M1** | Automation API OpenAPI + backend sync for `ThemeSpec` (`PORTAL_NEXT`) |
+| **M2** | Automation API OpenAPI + backend sync for `HomepageSpec` (`HOMEPAGE` area) |
+| **M3** | GKO CRDs + reconciliation |
+| **M4** | Terraform provider resources |
+
+---
+
+*Generated from [PORTAL-10](https://gravitee.atlassian.net/browse/PORTAL-10), related Jira tickets, and codebase analysis.*
